File: Gauteng premier David Makhura said on Tuesday that Gauteng will move to Level 3 at the beginning of June. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng premier David Makhura says the province will be easing lockdown restrictions in June. Speaking during a virtual legislature sitting on Tuesday, Makhura said Gauteng will move to Level 3 at the beginning of June. READ: Johannesburg not ready for Level 3: Makhubo He says the province has less than 15 percent of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the country, but the peak is still coming. Makhura says all districts in the country's economic hub will move together since they are highly integrated. READ: Decline in number of active COVID-19 cases in Gauteng: Makhura The provincial government will be meeting with stakeholders on Wednesday to prepare for Level 3. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.